The paper discusses the issue of software doping, which involves the intentional deviation of software from its main objective for dubious reasons. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and can also be related to computer security (cs.CR) as it involves malicious intent. The paper also discusses formal definitions and verification techniques, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper applies these techniques to reactive models, which fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
